Controller reference: deploy.yml patch note for /usage card
==============================================================

After investigation, **no changes to .github/workflows/deploy.yml are required**
for the /usage card feature to deploy correctly.

Why:
  - `npm run build` already includes the asset copy step:
        `... && mkdir -p dist/metrics/usage-render && cp -r src/metrics/usage-render/assets dist/metrics/usage-render/`
  - The existing `rsync -a --delete ... dist/ "$TARGET/dist/"` step (deploy.yml
    line 171-179) will transparently carry the new
    `dist/metrics/usage-render/assets/NotoSansKR.ttf` (~10MB) and LICENSE.
  - `rsync -a --delete node_modules/ "$TARGET/node_modules/"` (line 181) will
    carry the new `echarts` and `@resvg/resvg-js` dependencies. @resvg/resvg-js
    ships prebuilt native binaries per platform, and the self-hosted runner
    tag `oudwood-512` corresponds to the same host family that runs the
    staging/prod target, so the platform binary will match.

Operator action items:
  - After first deploy, verify font exists on remote:
        ls -lh $TARGET/dist/metrics/usage-render/assets/NotoSansKR.ttf
    Expected: ~10MB file.
  - Smoke-test in Slack staging:
        /usage card    (in any channel where bot is present)
    Expected: PNG card posted within 2-3 seconds.
  - If PNG render fails and logs show FontLoadError, check whether rsync
    excluded the asset dir (it shouldn't, but the only defensive fallback
    would be to add `--include='metrics/usage-render/assets/**'` explicitly —
    though with `-a` and no matching exclude, this is not currently needed).

No diff is required against deploy.yml — leaving this note for the record.
